text: Cat Records was a subsidiary of TK Productions whose flagship label was TK Records. It had no connections with the Cat Records label of the 1950s which was a division of Atlantic Records. It was founded in 1969 and lasted until 1980. Its most successful artist was Gwen McCrae. == External links == *Cat album discography Category:Defunct record labels of the United States Category:Record labels established in 1969 Category:Record labels disestablished in 1980
